{
  "texts": [
    "Advancements in on-chip technology, such as microfluidic chips or organoids, offer promising avenues for enhancing physiological data acquisition [71,72], providing detailed insights into physiological processes and facilitating refinement of RPT modeling and dosing strategies.",
    "Radiobiological dataDeveloping personalized TDTs for RPTs requires understanding crucial radiobiological phenomena influencing tumor cells and surrounding tissues [73][74][75].",
    "Factors include the tumor microenvironment, radiosensitivity, repair mechanisms, adaptive response, bystander effect, oxygenation, vasculature, repopulation, and redistribution.",
    "The tumor microenvironment significantly impacts tumor growth and RPT response, influenced by factors like hypoxia, pH, and nutrients.",
    "Radiosensitivity, indicating the intrinsic susceptibility of cells to radiation, must be considered in TDT modeling, emphasizing the need for a deeper integration of radiobiology into nuclear medicine practices [73][74][75][76][77]."
  ]
}